  "prompt": "If a contact has blocked me on their iPhone, and then they later decide to unblock me, will they then receive the messages I have sent to them?",
  "response": "When someone blocks you on their iPhone, any messages you send to them via iMessage or SMS will not be delivered to their device. If they later unblock you, they **will not** receive the messages you sent while you were blocked. Those messages are essentially lost and will not be delivered retroactively.\n\nHowever, after you\u2019ve been unblocked, any new messages you send will go through as normal, assuming you\u2019re still in each other\u2019s contacts and there are no other restrictions in place.\n\nKeep in mind that if you were blocked, there\u2019s no notification or indication when you\u2019ve been unblocked, so you\u2019ll only know if your messages are delivered and/or read in the future.",
